cEcEPARAGRAPH AND TEXT FORMATTING COMMANDS cEcA


    Commands that operate on paragraphs, and the layout of paragraphs:


cEParagraph  cA


    Paragraphs  are  separated by blank lines. A single  paragraph is defined as
    all of the text enclosed between two blank lines, with no intervening  blank
    lines.

    lsbackward-paragraph(2)lmbackward-paragraph(2)le (esc p) Move the cursor to the previous paragraph  
    lsfill-paragraph(2)lmfill-paragraph(2)le (esc o) Format a paragraph  
    lsforward-paragraph(2)lmforward-paragraph(2)le (esc n) Move the cursor to the next paragraph  
    lsifill-paragraph(3)lmifill-paragraph(3)le (esc q) Format a paragraph  
    lskill-paragraph(2)lmkill-paragraph(2)le Delete a paragraph  
    lsparagraph-to-line(3)lmparagraph-to-line(3)le Convert a paragraph to a single line  
    lswrap-word(2)lmwrap-word(2)le Wrap word onto next line  


