! 4 &opt
cEcENAME cEcA


    &opt - MicroEmacs optional feature test


cESYNOPSIS cA


    cD&optcA cCstrcA


cEDESCRIPTION cA


    This function can be used to test the availability of optional features in
    the current session of MicroEmacs. Some features, like spelling checker
    support, are a compilation option, other options like mouse support may
    also be unavailable on some platforms. The cD&optcA function can be used by
    macros to check that required base functionality is available.

    The function returns cG1cA in the given feature "cCstrcA" is supported, otherwise
    it returns cG0cA if the feature is unknown or not supported in the running
    version.


cENOTES cA


    Optional components of MicroEmacs 2009 are enabled/disabled at compile
    time, most options are configured by cGMEOPTcCcAcA<NAME>_ cG#definecA's within the
    source file cGemain.hcA. Following is a complete list of options, giving the
    cDoptcA string and cG#definecA label:

    abb - MEOPT_ABBREV
    
       Abbreviation functionality (see lsexpand-abbrev(2)lmexpand-abbrev(2)le).

    cal - MEOPT_CALLBACK
    
        Callback and idle event handling (see lscreate-callback(2)lmcreate-callback(2)le).

    fen - MEOPT_FENCE
    
        Fence matching (see lsfence(2m)lmfence(2m)le).

    cli - MEOPT_CLIENTSERVER
    
        Client/server support (see lsClient-Server(2)lmClient-Serverle).

    col - MEOPT_COLOR
    
        All color support (making hilighting redundent etc, see lsadd-color(2)lmadd-color(2)le).

    cry - MEOPT_CRYPT
    
        File encryption (see lscrypt(2m)lmcrypt(2m)le mode).

    deb - MEOPT_DEBUGM
    
        Macro debugging (see ls$debug(5)lm$debug(5)le).

    dir - MEOPT_DIRLIST
 
        Directory listing when loading a directory (see lsfile-browser(3)lmfile-browser(3)le and
        lsdir(2m)lmdir(2m)le mode ).

    ext - MEOPT_EXTENDED
 
        Miscellaneous more advanced commands and features such as
       lsappend-buffer(2)lmappend-buffer(2)le.
 
    fho - MEOPT_FILEHOOK
    
        File type auto-detection and configuration (see lsadd-file-hook(2)lmadd-file-hook(2)le).

    fra - MEOPT_FRAME
    
        Multiple frames (Internal or external, see opt "cDmwfcA" and command
        lscreate-frame(2)lmcreate-frame(2)le).

    has - MEOPT_CMDHASH
 
        Use a hash table for rapid command name lookup.

    hil - MEOPT_HILIGHT

        Hilight and user definable indentation rules (see lshilight(2)lmhilight(2)le and
        lsindent(2)lmindent(2)le).

    hsp - MEOPT_HSPLIT
    
       Horizontal window splitting (see lssplit-window-horizontally(2)lmsplit-window-horizontally(2)le).

    ipi - MEOPT_IPIPES
    
       Interactive pipes (see lsipipe-shell-command(2)lmipipe-shell-command(2)le).

    ise - MEOPT_ISEARCH
    
        Incremental search (see lsisearch-forward(2)lmisearch-forward(2)le).

    lbi - MEOPT_LOCALBIND
    
        Buffer, message-line and OSD local binding overrides (see
        lsbuffer-bind-key(2)lmbuffer-bind-key(2)le).

    mag - MEOPT_MAGIC
 
        Regular expression search engine (see lsmagic(2m)lmmagic(2m)le mode).

    mou - MEOPT_MOUSE
    
        Mouse support (see ls$mouse(5)lm$mouse(5)le).

    mwf - MEOPT_MWFRAME
    
        Multiple window frame support (see opt "cDfracA").

    nar - MEOPT_NARROW
 
        Buffer narrowing (see lsnarrow-buffer(2)lmnarrow-buffer(2)le).

    nex - MEOPT_FILENEXT

       Location list stepping (see lsget-next-line(2)lmget-next-line(2)le).

    osd - MEOPT_OSD
    
       On Screen Display GUI support (see lsosd(2)lmosd(2)le).

    pok - MEOPT_POKE
    
       Direct screen poking (see lsscreen-poke(2)lmscreen-poke(2)le).

    pos - MEOPT_POSITION
    
       Position storing and returning (see lsset-position(2)lmset-position(2)le).

    pri - MEOPT_PRINT
    
       Printing support (see lsprint-buffer(2)lmprint-buffer(2)le).

    rcs - MEOPT_RCS
    
       File Revision Control Support (see ls$rcs-co-com(5)lm$rcs-co-com(5)le).

    reg - MEOPT_REGISTRY
    
       Internal registry and history support (see lsread-registry(2)lmread-registry(2)le).

    scr - MEOPT_SCROLL
    
       Window scroll-bar support.

    soc - MEOPT_SOCKET
    
       URL support, FTP and HTTP via sockets (see lsfind-file(2)lmfind-file(2)le).

    spa - MEOPT_SPAWN
    
       External process launching (see lsshell-command(2)lmshell-command(2)le).

    spe - MEOPT_SPELL
    
       Spelling checker support (see lsspell(2)lmspell(2)le).

    tag - MEOPT_TAGS
    
       Tags support (see lsfind-tag(2)lmfind-tag(2)le).

    tim - MEOPT_TIMSTMP
    
       File timestamping on save (see lstime(2m)lmtime(2m)le mode).

    typ - MEOPT_TYPEAH
    
       Input detect or 'type-ahead' for background processing support.

    und - MEOPT_UNDO
    
       Undo support (see lsundo(2)lmundo(2)le).

    wor - MEOPT_WORDPRO
 
        Word-processor style commands like lsfill-paragraph(2)lmfill-paragraph(2)le (see
       lsforward-paragraph(2)lmforward-paragraph(2)le).


cEEXAMPLE cA


    The following example checks for URL support and if not available it pops
    up an error:

sB
          !if &not &opt "soc"
              osd-dialog "Opt Test" "Error: No URL support!" "  &OK  "
          !endif

sA
