! 5 $window-chars
cEcENAME cEcA


    $window-chars - Character set used to render the windows
$a


cESYNOPSIS cA


    cD$window-charscA "cCstingcA"; Default is
 cG`=-#*%=^|#|v*==^^||##||vv**|<-#->*||<<--##-->>** x*[]>\.$$\`cA


cEDESCRIPTION cA


    cD$window-charscA is a fixed length string that defines the set of characters
    used to render the windows. The characters have fixed indices defined as
    follows:-

    Index 0
 
       The active window mode line separator character, This replaces all
       cCIndex 1cA characters when the window is current. Default is 'cCcC=cAcA'.

    Index 1
 
       The inactive window mode line separator character. This character is
       replaced by cCIndex 0cA characters when the window becomes current.
       Default is 'cCcC-cAcA'.

    Index 2
 
       UNIX based platforms only. The cDrootcA or cDsuperusercA indicator character
       that appears on the mode line. Default is 'cCcC#cAcA'.

    Index 3
 
       The buffer changed indicator character that appears on the mode line.
       Default is 'cCcC*cAcA'.

    Index 4
 
       The buffer in lsview(2m)lmview(2m)le mode indicator character that appears in the
       mode line. Default is 'cCcC%cAcA'.

    Index 5
 
       Single column vertical scroll bar split window horizontally character.
       Default is 'cCcC=cAcA'.

    Index 6
 
       Single column vertical scroll bar up-arrow character. Default is 'cCcC^cAcA'.

    Index 7
 
       Single column vertical scroll bar upper-shaft character. Default is
       'cCcC|cAcA'.

    Index 8
 
       Single column vertical scroll box character. Default is 'cCcC#cAcA'.

    Index 9
 
       Single column vertical scroll bar lower-shaft character. Default is
       'cCcC|cAcA'.

    Index 10
 
       Single column vertical scroll bar down-arrow character. Default is
       'cCcCvcAcA'.

    Index 11
 
       Single column vertical scroll bar corner character. Default is 'cCcC*cAcA'.

    Index 12-13
 
       Double column vertical scroll bar split window horizontally character.
       Default is 'cD==cA'.

    Index 14-15
 
       Double column vertical scroll bar up-arrow characters. Default is "cD^cA".

    Index 16-17
 
       Double column vertical scroll bar upper-shaft characters. Default is
       "cD||cA".

    Index 18-19
 
       Double column vertical scroll box characters. Default is "cD##cA".

    Index 20-21
 
       Double column vertical scroll bar lower-shaft characters. Default is
       "cD||cA".

    Index 22-23
 
       Double column vertical scroll bar down-arrow characters. Default is
       "cDvvcA".

    Index 24-25
 
       Double column vertical scroll bar corner characters. Default is "cD**cA".

    Index 26-32
 
       Single column horizontal scroll bar. Default is "cD|<-#->*cA".

    Index 33-46
 
       Double column horizontal scroll bar. Default is "cD||<<--##-->>**cA".

    Index 47
 
       Osd title bar blank character. Default is 'cCcC cAcA'.

    Index 48
 
       Osd title bar right corner kill character. Default is 'cCcCxcAcA'.

    Index 49
 
       Osd dialog bottom right corner resize character. Default is 'cCcC*cAcA'.

    Index 50-53
 
       Osd button characters. 50 & 52 are used for a normal button, default
       is '__ cBButtoncA __'. 51 & 53 are used for the current default button,
       default is 'cD>cBButtoncA<cA'.

    Index 54
 
       Displayed tab character (used when ls$system(5)lm$system(5)le bit 0x80000 is set).
       Default is 'cCcC>cAcA'.

    Index 55
 
       Displayed new-line character (used when ls$system(5)lm$system(5)le bit 0x80000 is
       set). Default is 'cCcC\cAcA'.

    Index 56
 
       Displayed space character (used when ls$system(5)lm$system(5)le bit 0x80000 is set).
       Default is 'cCcC.cAcA'.

    Index 57
 
       Displayed truncated text to left character (used when the current line
       is scrolled to the right). Default is 'cCcC$cAcA'.

    Index 58
 
       Displayed truncated text to right character (used when the current
       line is longer than the window width). Default is 'cCcC$cAcA'.

    Index 59
 
       Inserted end of wrapped line character in an lsipipe-shell-command(2)lmipipe-shell-command(2)le
       buffer. Default is 'cCcC\cAcA'.


cEEXAMPLE cA


    The cD$window-charscA is typically platform dependent, it's setting is
    determined by the characters available in character set of the hosting
    platform. MS-DOS and Microsoft Windows use an OEM font might use the
    following value:

         "=-#*%=\C^\xB1 \xB1\C_\CD==\C^\C^\xB1\xB1  \xB1\xB1\C_\C_\C[
         \CZ|\CQ\xB1 \xB1\CP\CD||\CQ\CQ\xB1\xB1  \xB1\xB1\CP\CP\C[
         \CZ x*  >\\.$$\\"


    This utilizes character-set specific characters to render some of the
    window components.


cENOTES cA


    ls$scroll-bar(5)lm$scroll-bar(5)le allows the scroll box to be rendered in reverse video
     allowing a space to be used for the scroll box.
    
    Use lsinsert-symbol(3)lminsert-symbol(3)le to determine the displayable characters on the
    host platform.
    
    The use of MicroEmacs's extended character set on Windows and XTerm
    platforms can greatly improve the look and usability of MicroEmacs,
    see the Extend Char Set option in the Platform page of lsuser-setup(3)lmuser-setup(3)le
    and bit 0x10000 of variable ls$system(5)lm$system(5)le.


cESEE ALSO cA


    lssplit-window-horizontally(2)lmsplit-window-horizontally(2)le, lsinsert-symbol(3)lminsert-symbol(3)le, ls$box-chars(5)lm$box-chars(5)le,
    ls$global-scheme(5)lm$global-scheme(5)le, ls$mode-line(5)lm$mode-line(5)le, ls$mode-line-scheme(5)lm$mode-line-scheme(5)le, ls$scroll-bar(5)lm$scroll-bar(5)le,
    ls$scroll-bar-scheme(5)lm$scroll-bar-scheme(5)le, ls$system(5)lm$system(5)le.
