cESEE ALSO cA


    lscreate-frame(2)lmcreate-frame(2)le, lsdelete-frame(2)lmdelete-frame(2)le, lsnext-frame(2)lmnext-frame(2)le, ls$window-id(5)lm$window-id(5)le.
! 5 $window-id
cEcENAME cEcA


    $window-id - Current window identity


cESYNOPSIS cA


    cD$window-idcA


cEDESCRIPTION cA


    cD$window-idcA retrieves the identity of the current window, this is a integer
    value (1..n) that is automatically allocated when a window is created
    using lssplit-window-horizontally(2)lmsplit-window-horizontally(2)le or lssplit-window-vertically(2)lmsplit-window-vertically(2)le.

    The cD$window-idcA is guaranteed to be unique and is typically used in macros
