! 5 %fhook-f90-format
! 5 %fhook-f90-lint
cEcESYNOPSIS cEcA


    f, f77, f90 - Fortran files


cEFILES cA


    cDhkf90.emfcA - Fortran hook definition  
    cDf90.etfcA - Fortran 90 template file  
    cDf90.eafcA - Fortran 90 abbreviation file
    cDf.etfcA - Fortran (77) template file


cEEXTENSIONS cA


    cD.fcA - Fortran file  
    cD.f77cA - Fortran 77 file  
    cD.f90cA - Fortran 90 file


cEDESCRIPTION cA


    The cDf90cA file type templates provide simple hilighting of Fortran 77 and
    Fortran 90 files, the template provides minimal hilighting of both
    language syntaxes, which are overloaded into the same file.

    The major difference between the file types, apart from the new reserved
    words, is the comments. In Fortran 90 comments are introduced with cD!cA,
    while the other types use a cDccA in column 0.


    cDGeneral EditingcA
    
       On creating a new file, a new header is automatically included into
       the file. lstime(2m)lmtime(2m)le is by default enabled, allowing the modification
       time-stamp to be maintained in the header.

    cDHilightingcA
    
       The hilighting features allow functions, subroutines, variables, logical, comments,
       strings and characters of the language to be differentiated and
       rendered in different colors.

    cDFolding and Information HidingcA
    
       Generic folding is enabled within the cDf90cA files. The folds occur about
       cDfunctioncA, cDsubroutinecA, cDprogramcA,  and cDendcA text located on the left-hand margin.

      - lscollapse-all(3)lmcollapse-all(3)le - (un)folds  all regions in the file, 
      - lscollapse-current(3)lmcollapse-current(3)le - (un)folds the current region. 

    cDNavigation via Item ListcA

       The Fortan mode offers beside folding as well support for displaying
       an outline of the functions, subroutine, module and programp definitions
       of the Fortran file for easy  navigation using the lsitem-list(3)lmitem-list(3)le command.

    cDAbbreviationscA

       The  installation  comes with a default  abbreviation  file for Fortran 90
       file  editing  which  can  be  used  by  writing  short   abbreviations
       like   cC"if"cA  cC"wh"cA (while), or cC"fu"cA (function) - and then pressing
       the key-binding for the  lsexpand-abbrev-handle(3)lmexpand-abbrev-handle(3)le command.  
       The  list  of  abbreviations  can be used  interactively  in the GUI version of
       MicroEmacs using the lsabbrev-list(3)lmabbrev-list(3)le command.

    cDShort CutscA
    
       The short cut keys used within the buffer are:-

       cDC-c C-ccA - Comment out the current line.  
       cDC-c C-dcA - Uncomment the current line.  
       cDC-c esc esc cA- Command complete.  
       cDf2cA - (un)fold the current region  
       cDf3cA - (un)fold all regions  
       cDf6cA - Display the item list.
       cDesc f6cA - Hide the item list.

    cDExecuting, Formatting and LintingcA

      cD%fhook-fortran-execcA - The command to execute the current Fortran file, 
        default on Unix systems  is set to cC"gfortran %f -o %b && ./%b"cA where 
        cC%fcA represents the file name and cC%bcA the basename of the current file
        on Windows the slash is replaced with a backslash
              
      cD%fhook-fortran-formatcA - The command to format current Fortran file,
        default is set to cC"fprettify %"cA if the program is installed. 
        On a Unix system you might install it using the Python package manager
         like this: cC"pip3 install fprettify --user"cA.

      cD%fhook-fortran-lintcA - The command to check/lint the current Fotran file, 
         default is set to cC"gfortran -fsyntax-only %f"cA where cC%fcA represents
         the file name.
    
      The setting assume that the Gnu Fortran compiler and the cGfprettifycA formatter
      is available via the cCPATHcA environment variable. 
      On Windows you must insert here either the complete cCPATHcA to the 
      cGgfortrancA executable or add the folder where this file is to the cCPATHcA variable.

      These global variables should be changed if necessary usually within your cCUSERNAME.emfcA 
      or the cCmyfortran.emfcA file. 


cEBUGS cA


    The Fortran hilight file is in it's infancy and a number of it's tokens
    may be misplaced.


cESEE ALSO cA


    lsMicroEmacs - Supported File TypeslmSupported File Typesle
    lsabbrev-list(3)lmabbrev-list(3)le, lsexpand-abbrev-handle(3)lmexpand-abbrev-handle(3)le 
    lscollapse-all(3)lmcollapse-all(3)le, lscollapse-current(3)lmcollapse-current(3)le, 
    lsitem-list(3)lmitem-list(3)le, lstime(2m)lmtime(2m)le.
    
