cEcENAME cEcA

|%fhook-pascal-exec
    %fhook-paascal-exec - command to execute Pascal files
|%fhook-pascal-format
    %fhook-pascal-format - formatting command for Pascal files
|%fhook-pascal-lint
    %fhook-pascal-lint - linting command for Pascal files
$a

cESYNOPSIS cA


    p, pas - Pascal files  
    cD%fhook-pascal-execcA  
    cD%fhook-pascal-formatcA  
    cD%fhook-pascal-lintcA  


cEFILES cA


    cDhkpascal.emfcA - Pascal hook definition  
    cDpascal.eafcA - Pascal abbreviation file  
    cDpascal.etfcA - Pascal template file.


cEEXTENSIONS cA


    cD.pcA, cD.pascA - Pascal file


cEDESCRIPTION cA


    The cDpascalcA file type template provides simple hilighting of Pascal files,
    the template provides minimal hilighting.

    cDAbbreviationscA

       The  installation  comes with a default  abbreviation  file for Pascal file
       editing which  can  be  used  by  writing  short   abbreviations like
       "cCfocA" (for), "cCifcA", "cCelcA" (else), "cCprcA" (procedure)  or "cCwrcA" (writeln) - and then 
       pressing the key-binding  for the lsexpand-abbrev-handle(3)lmexpand-abbrev-handle(3)le command.

       The  list  of  abbreviations  can be used  interactively in the GUI version of
       MicroEmacs using the lsabbrev-list(3)lmabbrev-list(3)le command.

    cDFolding and Information HidingcA
    
       Generic folding is enabled within the Pascal files. The folds occur
       about  cDtypecA, cDfunctioncA or cDprocedurecA keywords and a closing cCend;cA, all at the
       beginning of a line. 

      - lscollapse-all(3)lmcollapse-all(3)le (un)folds all regions in the file, 
      - lscollapse-current(3)lmcollapse-current(3)le (un)folds the current region. 

    cDNavigation via Item ListcA

       The Pascal mode offers beside folding as well support for displaying an outline
       of the functions, procedures, records, objects and classes of the V file for easy navigation using the 
       lsitem-list(3)lmitem-list(3)le command. 

    cDWorking EnvironmentcA
    
       lscompile(3)lmcompile(3)le may be invoked to rebuild the source, the user is prompted
       to save any files.

    cDShort CutscA
    
       The short cut keys used within the buffer are:-

       cDC-c C-ccA - Comment out the current line.  
       cDC-c C-dcA - Uncomment the current line.  
       cDC-c C-ecA - Comment to the end of the line with stars (*).  
       cDA-C-icA - Restyle the current region.  
       cDesc qcA - Format a comment.  
       cDesc ocA - Format a comment.  
       cDf2cA - (Un)fold the current region.  
       cDf3cA - (Un)fold all regions.  
       cDf6cA - Display the item list.
       cDesc f6cA - Hide the item list.

    cDExecuting, Formatting and LintingcA
    
      cD%fhook-pascal-execcA - The command to execute the current Pascal file, default on Unix systems
              is set to cC"fpc %f && ./%b"cA where cC%fcA represents the file name and cC%bcA the
              basename of the current file on Windows the slash is replaced with a backslash
              
      cD%fhook-pascal-formatcA - The command to format current Pascal file, default  
              is set to cC"ptop %f temp.pas && cp temp.pas %f"cA on a Unix system
              where cC%fcA represents the file name, on Windows the cCcpcA command is
              replaced with cCcopycA
      cD%fhook-pascal-lintcA - The command to check/lint the current Pascal file, 
              default is set to cC"fpc -Cn %f"cA where cC%fcA represents the file name.
    
      The setting assume that the Free Pascal compiler and the cGptopcA formatter is available via the PATH
      environment variable. On Windows you must insert here either the complete PATH to the 
      cGfpccA executable or add the folder where this file is to the PATH variable.

      These global variables should be changed if necessary usually within your cCUSERNAME.emfcA 
      or the cCmypascal.emfcA file. 

cEBUGS cA


    None reported.


cESEE ALSO cA


    lsMicroEmacs - Supported File TypeslmSupported File Typesle,
    lsabbrev-list(3)lmabbrev-list(3)le, lsexpand-abbrev-handle(3)lmexpand-abbrev-handle(3)le.
