cEcESYNOPSIS cEcA


    *sh - UNIX shell files


cEFILES cA


    cDhkshell.emfcA - UNIX shell file hook definition  
    cDshell.eafcA   - UNIX shell abbreviation file  
    cDshell.etfcA   - UNIX shell programming language template file  


cEEXTENSIONS cA


    cD.shcA      - Bourne/Bash shell file  
    cD.kshcA     - Korn shell file  
    cD.cshcA     - C-Shell file  
    cD.zshcA     - Z-Shell file  
    cD.logincA   - Shell user login file  
    cD.profilecA - Shell user profile  
    cD.tcshrccA  - T-Shell start up file


cEMAGIC STRINGS cA


    cD#![ \t]*/.*shcA
    
    MicroEmacs 2009 recognizes the magic string on the first line of the
    file used to locate the executable. The shell files may be extension
    less and are still recognized. Note that this is the typical method of
    identifying shell files and will recognize other files not mentioned
    above i.e. cDbashcA shells.


cEDESCRIPTION cA


    The cDshellcA file type template provides simple hilighting of the shell
    files.  It offers as well folding and support for displaying and outline
    of the functions of the shell script for easy navigation using the 
    lsitem-list(3)lmitem-list(3)le  command and expanding abbreviations either via short 
    strings using the lsexpand-abbrev-handle(3)lmexpand-abbrev-handle(3)le command and visual
    inserting abbreviations using the lsabbrev-list(3)lmabbrev-list(3)le macro.

    cDFolding and Information HidingcA
    
       Generic folding is enabled within the Shell files. The folds occur about the
       function keyword and closing braces cGfunction...{...}cA located on the
       left-hand margin. The following commands are supported to show and hide
       the function bodies. 
       
       lscollapse-all(3)lmcollapse-all(3)le -  (un)folds all regions in the file,  
       lscollapse-current(3)lmcollapse-current(3)le - (un)folds the current region.

    cDList ItemscA

       Item listing is available and the key constructs of the file may be listed
       using  the lsitem-list(3)lmitem-list(3)le command.

    cDAbreviationscA

       The installation comes with a default abbreviation file for shell editing
       which can be used by writing short abbreviations like "cCforcA", "cCifcA" or "cCfuncA" - 
       for a Bourne shell or Z-shell function - and then pressing the key-binding for
       the lsexpand-abbrev-handle(3)lmexpand-abbrev-handle(3)le  command. The list
       of abbreviations can be used interactively in the GUI version of MicroEmacs
       using the  lsabbrev-list(3)lmabbrev-list(3)le command.

    cDShort CutscA
          
       The short cut keys used within the buffer are:-

       cDC-c C-ccA - Comment out the current line.  
       cDC-c C-dcA - Uncomment the current line.  
       cDC-c C-ecA - Comment to the end of the line with stars (*).  
       cDA-C-icA   - Restyle the current region.  
       cDesc qcA   - Format a comment.  
       cDesc ocA   - Format a comment.  
       cDf2cA      - (un)fold the current region  
       cDf3cA      - (un)fold all regions
       cDf6cA      - show the item-list outline
       cDEsc f6cA  - hide the item-list outline

cENOTES cA

    The file hook is implemented in the  cDshell.emfcA  file, the  abbreviations
    are placed within  the cDshell.eafcA file, the template for the initialization
    of the new file is defined in the  cDshell.etfcA file. To add your own
    abbreviations or your own template copy these files to your  config folder 
    and edit them within this folder.

cEBUGS cA


    Functions  defined without using the function  keyword can't currenly folded
    and as well do not appear in the item-list outline.

    There is a heavy bias towards Bourne, Korn and Zsh shells. The author is
    not a csh shell user so has probably missed a lot of csh features.


cESEE ALSO cA


    lsMicroEmacs - Supported File TypeslmSupported File Typesle, lsfvwm(9)lmfvwm(9)le.
! 9 java
! 9 jav
cEcESYNOPSIS cEcA


    java - Java programming language templates


cEFILES cA


    cDhkjava.emfcA - Java programming language hook definition  
    cDjava.eafcA - Java programming language abbreviatione file  
    cDjava.etfcA - Java programming language template file


cEEXTENSIONS cA


    cD.javacA, cD.javcA - Java


cEDESCRIPTION cA


    The cDjavacA file type templates share much with the lsc(9)lmc(9)le template
    definitions, utilising the electric 'C' features for automatic layout of
    text.

    cDGeneral EditingcA
    
       On creating a new file, a new header is automatically included into
       the file. lstime(2m)lmtime(2m)le is by default enabled, allowing the modification
       time-stamp to be maintained in the header.

    cDHilightingcA
    
       The hilighting features allow commands, variables, logical,
       preprocessor definitions, comments, strings and characters of the
       language to be differentiated and rendered in different colors.

    cDAuto LayoutcA
    
       The C-Mode lsindent(2)lmindent(2)le performs automatic layout of the text.

       lsrestyle-region(3)lmrestyle-region(3)le and lsrestyle-buffer(3)lmrestyle-buffer(3)le are available to reformat
       (re-layout) selected sections of the buffer, or the whole buffer,
       respectively.

       Comments may be formatted using `esc o`, which reformats the comments
       according to the current fill paragraph. If a comment commences with
       cG/***...cA then the comment is automatically formatted to a box.

    cDAbreviationscA

       The installation comes with a default abbreviation file for Java editing
       which can be used by writing short abbreviations like "cCfocA", "cCifcA" or "cCclcA" (class) 
       for Java classes functions. The list of abbreviations can be used as well interactively in the GUI
