cEcESYNOPSIS cEcA


    r - R Language File.


cEFILES cA


    cDhkr.emfcA - R language file hook definition  
    cDr.etfcA   - R template file  
    cDr.eafcA   - R abbreviation file

cEEXTENSIONS cA


    cD.rcA - R file  
    cD.RcA - R file  


cEMAGIC STRINGS cA


    cD^#![ \t]*/.*env[ \t]+RscriptcA
    
       MicroEmacs 2009 recognizes the magic string on the first line of the
       file used to locate the executable. The R files may be
       extension-less and are still recognized.


cEDESCRIPTION cA


    The cDRcA file type template provides simple hilighting of R files,
    the template provides minimal hilighting.

    File recognition is performed using the standard file extension cD.rcA, or cD.RcA or by
    the magic string.

    The R file hook offers as well folding and support for displaying an outline
    of the functions of the R script for easy navigation using the lsitem-list(3)lmitem-list(3)le command
    and expanding abbreviations either via short strings using the 
    lsexpand-abbrev-handle(3)lmexpand-abbrev-handle(3)le command and visually inserting abbreviations
    using the lsabbrev-list(3)lmabbrev-list(3)le macro.

    cDAbbreviationscA

       The installation comes with a default abbreviation file for R editing
       which can be used by writing short abbreviations like "cCforcA", "cCifcA" or "cCfunccA" - 
       for R functions. More extended abbreviations are "cCmaincA" for an Rscript
       application outline or "cCopenrcA" and "cCopenwcA" for reading and writing text files.
       The short strings  are then replaced by pressing the key-binding for the 
       lsexpand-abbrev-handle(3)lmexpand-abbrev-handle(3)le  command.
       The list of abbreviations can be used as well interactively in the GUI version 
       of MicroEmacs using the  lsabbrev-list(3)lmabbrev-list(3)le command.

    cDFolding and Information HidingcA
    
       Generic folding is enabled within the R files. The folds occur about the
       function definitions  located on the   left-hand  margin using the smaller-minus
       assignment operator. 
       The following  commands are supported to show and hide  the function bodies. 
       
       lscollapse-all(3)lmcollapse-all(3)le     - (un)folds all regions in the file,  
       lscollapse-current(3)lmcollapse-current(3)le - (un)folds the current region.

    cDNavigation via Item ListcA

       The R mode offers beside folding as well support for displaying an outline
       of the functions and classes of the R file for easy navigation using the 
       lsitem-list(3)lmitem-list(3)le command.

    cDShort CutscA
          
       The short cut keys used within the buffer are:-

       cDC-c C-ccA - Comment out the current line.  
       cDC-c C-dcA - Uncomment the current line.  
       cDC-c C-ecA - Comment to the end of the line with stars (*).  
       cDA-C-icA   - Restyle the current region.  
       cDesc qcA   - Format a comment.  
       cDesc ocA   - Format a comment.  
       cDf2cA      - (un)fold the current region  
       cDf3cA      - (un)fold all regions
       cDf6cA      - show the item-list outline
       cDEsc f6cA  - hide the item-list outline

cEBUGS cA


    There would appear to be too much applied hilighting in this file, it
    could probably do with rationalizing.


