    The cDrustcA file type templates share much with the lsc(9)lmc(9)le template definitions,
    utilising the electric 'C' features for automatic layout of text.

    cDGeneral EditingcA
    
       On creating a new file, a new header is automatically included into
       the file. lstime(2m)lmtime(2m)le is by default enabled, allowing the modification
       time-stamp to be maintained in the header.

    cDHilightingcA
    
       The hilighting features allow commands, variables, logical,
       preprocessor definitions, comments, strings and characters of the
       language to be differentiated and rendered in different colors.

    cDAuto LayoutcA
    
       The C-Mode lsindent(2)lmindent(2)le performs automatic layout of the text.

       lsrestyle-region(3)lmrestyle-region(3)le and lsrestyle-buffer(3)lmrestyle-buffer(3)le are available to reformat
       (re-layout) selected sections of the buffer, or the whole buffer,
       respectively.

