       Generic folding is enabled within the Rust files. The folds occur
       about the cDfncA keyword and a closing curly brace, both at the
       beginning of a line. Furthermore cDimplcA sections for method definitions
       of classes are foldable. 
       
       - lscollapse-all(3)lmcollapse-all(3)le (un)folds all regions in the file,
       - lscollapse-current(3)lmcollapse-current(3)le (un)folds the current region. 

